geo:siteIdentification.geo:notes: Gilmore Creek NOAA/ NESDIS Geological Province-Central Mainland Alaska. Paleozoic metamorphic rocks. Geological information from "NASA Space Geodesy Program Catalogue of Site Information", Technical Memorandum 4482, March 1993, p120.

geo:CollocationInformation.geo:notes: 26 m dish remains standing. Day and month of decommissioning are unknown. Three brass survey markers are set in VLBI foundation.
Antenna was located on roof of Gilmore Creek Geophysical Observatory ops building. Antenna is no longer in place. Exact dates of installation and decomissioning unknown.
FAIC rooftop single mast monument. Antenna has Javad Delta and Trimble NetRS receivers attached via a splitter.
GCGO deep drilled single mast monument. Antenna has Javad Delta receiver attached. GCGO is located 100 feet due NW from FAIR.
